Here is an example of a Discord bot written in Discord.js v14 using slash commands:

```js
const Discord = require("discord.js");
const bot = new Discord.Client();

bot.on("ready", () => {
  console.log("Ready!");
});

bot.on("message", message => {
  if (message.content === "/ban") {
    const user = message.mentions.users.first();
    if (user) {
      message.channel.send(`Ban ${user} from this channel.`);
    } else {
      message.channel.send("Please mention a user to ban.");
    }
  }
});
```
This example creates a Discord bot using the `Discord` npm package, then initializes it with the `new Discord.Client()` function and adds event listeners for the `ready` and `message` events. The `on("message")` listener checks the message content for the `/ban` command and executes the appropriate action depending on whether or not the user is mentioned in the message.

